-- Sinotruk plans up to $1.2 billion Hong Kong IPO, source says
-- 
-- Sun Nov 11, 2007 7:38pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/11/12/us-sinotruk-ipo-idUSHKG30614020071112

 

 HONG KONG  (Reuters) - China's top heavy truck maker, Sinotruk (Hong Kong) Ltd, plans to raise up to US$1.2 billion from its Hong Kong initial public offering, a source familiar with the deal said on Monday. 

 The company, which kicks off a marketing roadshow for its IPO on Monday, is offering 702 million shares, or 32 percent of its enlarged share capital, with a price range of HK$10-HK$12.88 each, the source said. JP Morgan ( JPM.N ) and China International Capital Corp Ltd are sponsoring the deal. (US$1=HK$7.8) (Reporting by Kennix Chim; editing by  Dominic Whiting )